				<td colspan="2"><span>I am in a guild that can get my epic 1.5 and even the 2.0 (we have a few members who are 1 or 2 kills away from their 2.0s) but I am not motivated to press my guildmates to help me with the fights when the reward is a reduction in most of my worn mods.  The stats of 1.5 weren't meant to wow an end-game guild but the fights are too cumbersome for the EP guilds who would benefit.
<br />

<br />
Even if the epic 2.0 has a 2.8 mod for all instruments and that Verse effect, it's not worth burdening the guild who is already stretched thin with signets, more useful epic fights for other classes, holidays, WoW, and EQ2.  Most guilds who can get 2.0 are toppling on the edge of burnout and dealing with attrition, and no bard in their right mind is going to demand epic help on top of everything else.  Besides, if I just keep going to raids, I'll get a Tacvi rapier and the Edge from Zun'Muram.  Then I'll have a 2.9 percussion mod and a 2.8 singing mod, and I'm not too concerned about the rest.  When was the last time someone said after an MPG raid, &quot;Man, that HP regen from manasong really made a difference.  I'm so glad you bothered to equip your lute.&quot;  Wind is more useful to me in the end game than string, but I have my eye on the Organic ring anyway.  
<br />

<br />
So that's my perspective as a bard in a guild who could go after my epic 2.0.
<br />

